<H3>Course objectives</H3>
<UL>
  <LI> Become familiar with the DLXS middleware (including searching with XPat, 
    document classes, and how to modify the middleware). <A HREF="objectives.html" TARGET="mainFrame">Objectives 
    details</A>.</LI>
</UL>
<H3>Prerequisites</H3>
<UL>
  <LI>some familiarity with SGML</LI>
  <LI>familiarity with perl5</LI>
  <LI>have seen the kinds of online collections DLPS makes available already (see 
    <A href="http://www.umdl.umich.edu/" target="external">http://www.umdl.umich.edu/</A> 
    and <A href="http://www.hti.umich.edu/" target="external">http://www.hti.umich.edu/</A> 
    for examples)</LI>
  <LI>have the XPAT package from DLXS</LI>
  <LI>Note: during the workshop, we will provide data, already indexed and ready 
    for use. Information on data preparation can be found at: <A href="/dlxs/training/workshop-user-2000.html" target="external">DLXS 
    Public Service &amp; Text Encoders Workshop</A><BR>
  </LI>
</UL>
